<h2>&#x221a;kū<i> 'design'</i></h2><p>
<i>present: </i><b>kuvate</b> &#xa0;[2.] <b>kauti</b> &#xa0;</p><p>
<i>verbal: </i><b>-kūta</b> <sub>AV.+ </sub>&#xa0;<b>-kā́vam</b> &#xa0;</p><p>
<i>derivatives: </i><b>-kūti</b> <sub>V.+ </sub>&#xa0;<b>kaví</b> <sub>V.+ </sub>&#xa0;<b>kávīyas</b> <sub>SV. </sub>&#xa0;</p><p>
Used only with <b>ā</b>, except in <b>niṣkā́vam</b>, the belonging of which is doubtful (as is also that of <b>kaví</b>).  RV. has -<b>kava</b>, <b>kavatnú</b>, <b>kavārí</b>, 'stingy', of questionable relationship.  The grammarians set up roots 1<b>ku</b>, 2<b>ku</b> or <b>kū</b>, 'shout', giving them a full set of forms; and Nir. once uses their intens. <b>kokūyate</b>.</p></body>
